The monitor's controls are driving me so crazy that I might return it
and get the HP ZR2740w.  I have another week or two to decide.

I physically can't lift my arms without a lot of pain.  I want to
change brightness in the morning and at night without having to reduce
contrast.

The Viewsonic has a bad menu system for controlling brightness, and
you have to switch to Eco mode with lower contrast to get low levels
of brightness.  The HP has no menu system.  However, both monitors
have the specs that I need for other reasons.  There aren't many other
options.

Will either of these monitors work with ddccontrol?  What can I
control?  Also, is integrated Intel graphics supported?

Thank you VERY much.


